---
/**
 * consistent-hashing-deep-dive · Figure 3 — "ADD a node steals ONE arc".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source HTML (figure + svg + figcaption). Isolated as
 * an .astro component. It references marker-end="url(#arwG)"; that arrowhead
 * marker (fill #2f5d3a) was declared once in the source's top-of-body <svg defs>
 * and is inlined here in a local <defs> so the figure resolves standalone.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 230"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Adding node N5 between N1 and N2 claims only the arc behind it — keys move from one neighbour, everything else stays"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="300"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">ADD a node → it steals ONE arc from its predecessor</text
            >
            <!-- BEFORE ring -->
            <text
                x="150"
                y="44"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#6b675f">before</text
            >
            <circle cx="150" cy="140" r="70" fill="none" stroke="#6b675f" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle>
            <circle cx="150" cy="70" r="8" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle><text
                x="150"
                y="60"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">N1</text
            >
            <circle cx="220" cy="140" r="8" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle><text
                x="236"
                y="144"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">N2</text
            >
            <circle cx="150" cy="210" r="8" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle><text
                x="150"
                y="226"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">N3</text
            >
            <!-- arc owned by N2 highlighted -->
            <path
                d="M 150 70 A 70 70 0 0 1 220 140"
                fill="none"
                stroke="#1f3a5a"
                stroke-width="4"
                opacity="0.4"></path>
            <text x="150" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#1f3a5a">N2 owns</text>
            <text x="150" y="152" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#1f3a5a">this arc</text>
            <!-- arrow between -->
            <line x1="248" y1="140" x2="350" y2="140" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"
            ></line>
            <text x="299" y="130" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >insert N5</text
            >
            <!-- AFTER ring -->
            <text
                x="460"
                y="44"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#6b675f">after</text
            >
            <circle cx="460" cy="140" r="70" fill="none" stroke="#6b675f" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle>
            <circle cx="460" cy="70" r="8" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle><text
                x="460"
                y="60"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">N1</text
            >
            <circle cx="530" cy="140" r="8" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle><text
                x="546"
                y="144"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">N2</text
            >
            <circle cx="460" cy="210" r="8" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle><text
                x="460"
                y="226"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">N3</text
            >
            <circle cx="520" cy="92" r="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle><text
                x="540"
                y="86"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">N5</text
            >
            <!-- arc stolen by N5 -->
            <path
                d="M 520 92 A 70 70 0 0 1 530 140"
                fill="none"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="4"
                opacity="0.55"></path>
            <text x="460" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >N5 takes only</text
            >
            <text x="460" y="152" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >this slice (~K/N)</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Lookup = a <em>successor search</em>: binary-search the sorted node positions for the next
        one clockwise → <code>O(log N)</code>. Remove a node and its arc falls to its clockwise
        successor — again ~K/N keys, to one node.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
